description:
Each map includes a graphics layer with the same graphics, but the map on the left uses static rendering mode, and the map on the right uses dynamic rendering mode. A graphics layer that renders in static mode refreshes the graphics at the end of the animation, whereas a graphics layer rendering in dynamic mode refreshes throughout the animation. Each mode has its own strengths and weaknesses, depending on the number of graphics, complexity of geometry, and the device's GPU memory and power.
